def: A genus of plants (herbs, shrubs, or trees), some species ofwhich have large, showy flowers. Some species are cultivated in Indiafor their fiber, which is used as a substitute for hemp. See Althea,Hollyhock, and Manoe.
Given to tricks; artful in making bargains; given to deceptionand cheating; knavish.-- Trick"ish*ly, adv.-- Trick"ish*ness, n.
A genus of orchidaceous plants including the lady's slipper.
A treatise on, or description of, coins and medals.
A place set apart for equestrian and chariot races.
The state or quality of being reliable; reliableness.
A horizontal bar on a stake, used for supporting the yarnswhich are kept apart by pins in the bar.
A suborder of primates, including the lemurs, the aye-aye, andallied species. [Written also Lemuroida.]
A foot of three long syllables. [Written also molosse.]
